name: Cucumber and Olive Appetizers
author: Gwena Hedlund
summary: I got this recipe from one of my cooking classes in college.  It's the "old fashioned" type of appetizer, but one that makes a beautiful display on the plate and I never take any home with me because they disappear quickly.
ingredients: ¼ cup blue cheese salad dressing
directions: Using the tines of a fork, score the unpeeled cucumber lengthwise on all sides
Slice the cucumber into 1/4-inch thick rounds
In a small bowl, combine the cream cheese and blue cheese dressing
Spread the cheese mixture on the rye bread slices
Top with a slice of cucumber and a slice of olive
